i am a bit late but here's the explanation:  Measure the slope of the curve in consideration. The formula for slope is tan(theta) where theta is measured in anti clockwise direction. You will find that the angle at all points is constant. Therefore, tan(theta) is constant, hence slope is constant, therefore velocity (which is given by slope of x-t graph) is constant. That implies change in velocity is zero and acceleration is change in velocity per unit time, therefore it's zero as well.

Your meaning of a positive acceleration as increasing velocity (speeding up) and negative acceleration as decreasing velocity (slowing down) are misleading and are common misconceptions in Physics. The truth is that +a can also mean slowing down and that a negative acceleration can also mean speeding up. You forgot to consider that acceleration is a vector quantity. A common example is the up and down motion of a body thrown straight up and which comes down. The acceleration which is due to gravity is g= -9.8 m/s^2 whether it is moving up (slowing down) or moving down (speeding up).
